description:
This data extraction template is designed as a starting point for health professions education researchers conducting a knowledge synthesis. It outlines commonly used fields. However, it is not a one-size-fits-all solution nor is it comprehensive.&nbsp; 
 &nbsp; 
 Researchers should adapt the template to align with their specific aims, the type of knowledge synthesis they are undertaking (e.g., systematic review, scoping review, realist review), and the nature of the evidence they are analyzing. Tailoring this template to each project ensures it captures the most relevant information for answering the research question and supports consistent, rigorous data extraction across studies. 
 &nbsp; 
 Published in Medical Teacher, 2025. DOI:10.1080/0142159X.2025.2551252

